sentences: Benny Turner (born October 27, 1939) is an American blues musician.
Turner was born in Gilmer, Texas on October 27, 1939.
In the 1950s, Turner moved to Chicago with his family.

Later, Turner moved to New Orleans and became the bandleader for Marva Wright in 1986, playing with her band for 20 years.
After Wright's death in 2010, Turner went on to release four albums including his critically acclaimed 2014 album of original work called Journey.
After Wright's death in 2010, Turner went on to release four albums including his critically acclaimed 2014 album of original work called Journey.
His 2016 album When She's Gone was dedicated to his mother Ella Mae and featured a collection of six original reissues from his album, Blue and Not So Blue, and four blues standards.
His autobiography, Survivor : The Benny Turner Story, was published on July 8, 2017.
Also in 2017, Turner released his latest album, My Brother's Blues.
In 2019, Turner  joined forces with longtime friend and fellow Chicago musician Cash McCall to record Going Back Home, revisiting their days of playing on Chicago's South and West Sides.
On October 27, 2019, Turner celebrated his 80th birthday at the Inaugural Lone Star Blues and Heritage Festival in Grapeland, Texas.
